title: Test
summary: This is a multi-line chart with 2 lines representing Male, and Female.
The line for Male has the highest values across Year with a mean value of 20.65,
and it peaked at 75_years_and_over with a value of 45.51.
Female mostly had the least y-axis name with a mean value of 1.27,
which peaked at 55_to_64_years with a value of 1.75.
Overall Male is rapidly increasing, Female is roughly constant,  throughout the Year
The difference of y_axis name between Male and Female is greater at Year 75_years_and_over compared to the Year 18_to_34_years.
The greatest difference of y_axis name between Male and Female occurs at Year 75_years_and_over and the smallest difference occurs at 18_to_34_years.
